  "texts": [
    "If so, the step current input that it causes in layer n is, in our implementation, only taken into account for t > t ðnÀ1Þ min, see Eq.",
    "(1), even though the neuron has fired at t ðnÀ1Þ j < t ðnÀ1Þ min.",
    "In other words, the spike is sent immediately to the next layer, where it triggers the step current input, but the input is blocked until time t ðnÀ1Þ min.",
    "This implementation enables us to consider overlapping spiking phases across subsequent layers.",
    "To quantify, how much we can make the spiking phases in layer n -1 and n overlap, we studied the mapping to the corresponding ReLU network and exploited that early firing times in the SNN correspond to ReLU units with high activity."
